---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="How to Encourage Your Customers to Be More Sustainable - parcelLab"
  description="Practical strategies for e-commerce brands to support customers in making more sustainable purchasing and delivery decisions."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Sustainability</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">How to Encourage Your Customers to Be More Sustainable</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2022-09-13">September 13, 2022</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Does sustainability still matter to consumers? With inflation rising and supply problems hitting hard, is sustainable e-commerce still a priority? The answer is yes -- for most industries. Over half of consumers still say that sustainability is an important part of how they make purchase decisions.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">How to Encourage Sustainable Behavior</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The easiest way to encourage sustainability is by making it the simple, default choice. It should be easy to identify sustainable products, choose sustainable delivery options, and find out how to reduce waste and carbon emissions. Your first task as a sustainable e-commerce business is to be transparent, direct, and helpful.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Reward Sustainable Decisions</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Offer discounts or loyalty points for sustainable choices. Make non-sustainable choices more difficult. When major supermarkets in the UK started charging for single-use plastic bags, usage dropped significantly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Offer Repair and Sharing Services</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Reduce over-consumption by offering repair or sharing services. The future of sustainable retail is a circular economy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Sustainable Delivery Options</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              A substantial portion of UK shoppers report they're more likely to choose retailers with sustainable delivery services. Offer greener shipping alternatives at checkout.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Layer Sustainability Information</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              If someone clicks to read more about one sustainable product, follow up with more targeted offers or information about sustainable options.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Keeping Your End of the Deal</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Over a third of UK shoppers would pay more for products that support sustainability and social justice. And 1 in 3 UK shoppers say they've actively blacklisted a brand because of concerns about those values.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The biggest target for sustainability in e-commerce is packaging and delivery. Around 165 billion packages are shipped each year in the US alone. It takes a billion trees to produce that much cardboard.
        </p>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          E-commerce retailers can support sustainability by:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Switching single-use packaging for recyclable and reusable options</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Choosing more efficient packaging designs that use less material</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Choosing sustainable delivery providers, such as electric vehicles</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Leveraging tech to create more efficient supply chains and delivery systems</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          If you want to improve customer satisfaction and sustainability at the same time, upgrading your operations tech can make a huge difference. It might not have the immediate appeal of fresh packaging or a fleet of e-bikes, but it can identify and improve sustainability at every level of your business.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
